rComments: Professor Lenard is the most caring professor I've had at uOttawa in the past 5 years. She is engaging and despite thinking she is old, she connects with students so easily. She is passionate about teaching and truly wants students to understand the material to be able to apply it in the real world. She is also very flexible and understanding!

One of the best professors that I have ever had. I definitely recommend that future first-year GSPIA students take her class rather than skip out on it and take Ethics with another professor. Professor Lenard is amazing, cares about her students, and if you follow her guidelines to the letter it is easy to get decent marks. Be prepared to learn!

Lenard is very passionate about her content and it is very refreshing compared to the rest of uOttawa professors. Lenard also needs sensitivity training when interacting with students. She thinks everyone understands what she says and that ambiguity that is far off from her intention is absurd to the point she will point it out to the entire class
Best prof I've ever had! Made a subject I could care less about super interesting!! Loved her course and would gladly take any class she teaches just to have her as a prof again

Prof Lenard is hilarious in her lectures and goes off on tangents a lot but always gets through all of the material. She makes lectures fun and engaging. Assignments are simple but some of the readings are boring. Great prof!
I can't believe she made me like political philosophy. Great lectures, makes the readings easy to understand, and the DGDs were super helpful, too. I hope I have another class with her!

Patti Lenard is one of the best professors in FSS. She is considerate and kind, the course content get brought to life and she facilitates amazing discussions. She gets to know her students, and she, when discussing ethics, does not put her personal preference into it, but lets the work speak for itself. Id gladly take any class she teaches.

I love this professor! She is so intelligent but also explains complicated subjects in a way that makes sense easily. She is very dedicated to her students and cares about their experience. I would take her again!!

Professor Lenard is an extremely intelligent individual and genuinely cares for her students. Her grading criteria is unclear so that is a downside with her. Participation does matter in class but she does facilitate good discussions.

I loved the evaluation distribution she did. Online quizzes throughout the semester worth 35%, a midterm, participation in DGDs, and an essay. No final. Shes an amazing lecturer and is very fun and engaging. LOTS of long and very dense readings which were brutal.

Professor Lenard's class was the first (and only) class during my entire degree for which I completed every reading. She's engaging, challenging, and extremely intelligent. You are guaranteed to learn a ton in her class. It's a heavy workload but if you're interested in the topic and up for the challenge, it's definitely worth it.
Enseignante très interessante et ouverte aux débats et discussions. Très compréhensive et à l'écoute de ses élèves, ainsi que prête à les aider n'importe quand ! Très bon cours.

Professor Lenard is an accomplished scholar, who challenges her students, but provides them the tools to be successful. Her passion and ability to capture the attention of her students, and convey the material in an interesting way is unique. She allows students to develop their own arguments and engage in dialogue within a moderated structure.

Professor Lenard is an adept and thoughtful philosopher. Be prepared to participate and be challenged. You will learn a lot in her seminars. 10/10 would recommend that all ECH students take a 4th year seminar with her.

A lowball grader. Grading criteria is vague yet expectations are very specific. Participation counts for a huge part of your mark and the grading for this is questionable and inconsistent. Not helpful in office hours and is condescending when students ask for clarification (very unprofessional).

Lenard is a tough grader;  visits during office hours provide no clarification. Grading criteria is unclear. Mocks students in front of the class and actively grades you while you speak (intimidating). Participation really, really matters, so you have to do the readings in detail in order to participate fully. Subject matter is interesting.

Prof is great, super passionate, I really wanted to like this class but I just did not. Material is so dry, but she does an alright job of making it interesting. Pop quizzes suck, she told us she does not like doing them either, so hopefully she takes it out of the syllabus.

Readings are very long and you cannot do well without attending lectures. Pop quizzes are on specifics of the readings which makes them hard to complete well. Great prof for lectures. Really engaging and takes the time to know the students that participate. Only problem is I went to her office hours and she didn't seem too keen to help.

Super sweet lady! Although the reading material she assigns is rather long and not the most interesting, when she talks it over in class it makes a lot more sense. She has a way of making an otherwise dull text very exciting. She is so enthusiastic about what she teaches and is hands down one of the nicest profs I've had.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read', 'Hilarious']

rComments: Splendid person and professor! She is very kind and hilarious. However, this class requires a lot of reading that is difficult and very long. She is an excellent lecturer and makes the content very easy to understand. Make sure you do your readings before class!

An amazing professor, she made material that would otherwise be exceptionally boring so interesting and easy to understand! She is sweet and funny, the only downfall is the heavy and difficult reading load.

Amazing prof. Content of the class was awful and there were a lot of readings, however Professor Lenard had amazing lectures and made it all worth while. She was very fair and you always knew what was expected of you. I would 100% take another class with her!

I really appreciate the professor's humour, encouragement and passion. She makes an otherwise dry subject engaging, encourages students to participate and truly tries to get to know them in the process, which is so respected. Her passion is evident in her lectures. Similar to another student, I had TA problems. Overall, it was a great experience.

Professor Lenard is a great prof.  She is clearly knows what she's talking about and effectively conveys class material to the class. Her lectures are stimulating and interesting. I attended to ALL of her classes. However, you have to do a lottttt of reading in this class, and they are definitely not easy reads.

An amazingly inspiring prof that is clearly in love with the content. Is very effective at conveying material and letting you come to your own conclusions. Marking was fair and the readings could get long but were vital to the course. Would 100% recommend

Just a disclaimer: Lenard is an awesome professor. She is enthusiastic and passionate which made her lectures my favourite to attend this semester. I had a horrible experience with a TA but thats not her fault. The course load is heavy: expect a lot of reading and keep up. One of the most demanding courses I've taken. Buckle down

90% of the readings are posted on blackboard so no expensive textbook needed. The readings are long and dry, but Lenard is such and engaging and passionate lecturer it's much easier to comprehend. DGDs everyou few weeks allow students to really discuss their understanding. Pop quizzes to ensure you've read, so attend lectures- they're great anyway!

She is very inspirational and loves her job, which makes it easier to go to class. Amen. I also like that you do not have to purchase a book as the readings are all online. The downside (but smart on her part): You must do every new reading before every class as she does a POP QUIZ at least five times to do attendance. So you sorta have to attend.

Patti Lenard is one of my favorite professors at the University of Ottawa. Her passion, interest, and delivery of the subject is incredible. For a Friday morning seminar, you actually didn't want to miss it. It is strongly recommended to take at least one of her classes. Be prepared to work, and read, but you will be rewarded for it, in the end.
Amazing prof, always there to help you out if you need it Lectures are unreal, she makes them fun and interesting MidtermsExam are fair. You'll get a good mark as long as you understand the material.

Patti is the best professor EVER! That's not even an exaggeration since I had many awesome profs this semester. She's reasonable, reliable, and hilarious to boot. She explains difficult readings with such ease and really makes you love learning about otherwise boring material. Put in some effort, show interest, and prosper! Best prof at uOttawa!

One of the best professors at uOttawa, actually cares about the students and makes sure we all succeed. Need to do every reading on time to understand class material. She does not give her opinions and lets you make your own, suggesting that if it's well justified, it can be right. This was a Global Ethics class - awesome class!

Patti is a fantastic professor...she took subject matter that had the potential to be very dry and gave it life. She's personable and witty and her lectures are always entertaining.  Her personality fills the lecture hall!  Exams and essays were fair and she's very approachable if you need help.
I would have struggled with the readings for this course if Patti didn't do such an amazing job on conveying the central ideas to us in class. She's wonderful!!

Absolutely phenomenal!  She loves teaching (especially this course) and makes all the material really interesting no matter what it is.  She was so funny and entertaining during lectures that the class would always be full and everyone would be paying attention.  Take this course with her if you can!

Best professor I've had by far! She is incredibly entertaining while explaining the most boring, dry material. She really cares about her students, and tries to accommodate any requests to improve the course. If you have the chance to take a class with her, take it!!

Really incredible professor, she takes really dry subject matter and makes it come to life. Cannot recommend highly enough, because of her I got my first ever A+ in a course I usually struggle with. Also very funny, you can tell she really knows her stuff and is comfortable addressing all manner of questions.
Absolutely incredible in class - she is very clear and makes complex theories easily understandable. ABSOLUTELY RUDE when approached, stick to not asking questions out of class and you'll be fine..
Great prof! Really passionate about a variety of issues in DVM and clearly loves teaching.

Does an excellent job at explaining political thought, and making it interesting! If you attend the lectures she explains the ideas excellently, but her powerpoints are sparse so don't depend on them. Funny, interesting prof, who's class I very much enjoyed.
An excellent professor. Very committed to her students and teaching. Makes class interesting and tries her best to make sure students understand complex ideas,philosophies, and theories.
